<p>"<b>Being for the Benefit of Mr. Kite!</b>" is a song from the 1967 album by <a href="/wiki/The_Beatles" title="The Beatles">the Beatles</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/Sgt._Pepper%27s_Lonely_Hearts_Club_Band" title="Sgt. Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band">Sgt. Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band</a>.</i> It was primarily written and composed by <a href="/wiki/John_Lennon" title="John Lennon">John Lennon</a>, although <a href="/wiki/Paul_McCartney" title="Paul McCartney">Paul McCartney</a> claims that he also contributed to it.<sup id="cite_ref-FOOTNOTEMiles1997318_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-FOOTNOTEMiles1997318-2">[2]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-macca_3-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-macca-3">[3]</a></sup> The song is credited to <a href="/wiki/Lennon%E2%80%93McCartney" title="Lennon–McCartney">Lennon–McCartney</a>.</p>
<p></p>
<div id="toc" class="toc">
<div id="toctitle">
